  "privacyPolicyIntro": "Classmate currently works as a local-first app. Timetable data, timetable settings, and period-time data are stored on your device or in your browser by default. The app only uses system capabilities such as import, export, sharing, or opening external links when you explicitly trigger those actions.",
  "privacyPolicyLocalStorageTitle": "Local storage",
  "privacyPolicyLocalStorageBody": "On Android, iOS, Windows, macOS, and Linux, the app stores timetable data and related settings in a local file named classmate_data.json inside the app documents directory. On the web, the app stores the same kind of data in browser storage. The app does not upload this data to a developer-controlled server by default.",
  "privacyPolicyImportExportTitle": "Import and export",
  "privacyPolicyImportExportBody": "The app only reads or writes timetable JSON files and period-template files when you explicitly choose a file or start an export action. Imported file contents are only used to create or update timetable data locally.",
  "privacyPolicySharingTitle": "Sharing",
  "privacyPolicySharingBody": "When you explicitly use sharing, the app passes the exported file to the system share sheet or to the target app you choose. How that file is handled afterward depends on the target app or service you selected.",
  "privacyPolicyExternalLinksTitle": "External links",
  "privacyPolicyExternalLinksBody": "When you open external links such as the GitHub repository, the app hands the action off to your browser or another external application. Data handling after that point is governed by the third party you open.",
  "privacyPolicyNoCollectionTitle": "What is not collected right now",
  "privacyPolicyNoCollectionBody": "In the current version, the app does not require an account and does not collect school account passwords, cloud backup data, advertising identifiers, or analytics data by default.",
  "privacyPolicyFutureFeatureTitle": "Future feature notice",
  "privacyPolicyFutureFeatureBody": "A future version may support importing courses from a school timetable webpage when you explicitly start that process. If that feature introduces new data handling, network requests, or additional information requirements, this policy will be updated before the feature is released.",
  "privacyPolicyUpdatesTitle": "Policy updates",
  "privacyPolicyUpdatesBody": "The current privacy policy version is {version}. If a future version changes how data is handled, the app may ask you to read and agree to the updated policy again.",
